                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#5r">5r</locus> (incipit page of Text I): simple ornamental
                        band with one central pendant; interlaces and anthropomorphic motifs. The
                        number ፩ (quire mark?) and several letters are written in the centre of the
                        band.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Monthly readings are indicated by the names of the
                              months written in the upper margin: ዘኅዳር: <locus target="#7ra">fol.
                                 7ra</locus> ዘየካቲት: <locus target="#22rb">fol. 22rb</locus> ዘመጋቢት:
                                 <locus target="#25rb">fol. 25rb</locus> ዘሰኔ: <locus target="#43ra">fol. 43ra</locus> (in the text) ዘነሐሴ: <locus target="#52rb">fol.
                                 52rb</locus> ዘመስከረም: <locus target="#55ra">fol. 55ra</locus> ዘጥቅምት:
                                 <locus target="#57ra">fol. 57ra</locus>. There might have been
                              indications also for the other months, written on the part of
                              parchment eaten by rodents.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- Omitted letters or words are written interlineally: e.g., fols. 13ra, 18ra, 22rb. - Scribal mistakes are indicated by series of dashes or parallel lines around the erroneous word, in different hands: fols. 9ra, 17ra, 17va, 25va, 41ra, 55ra. - Corrections inserted interlineally, in recent hands: e.g., fols. 13va, 14ra, 60v, 61ra. - Crude drawings and scribbles: fols. 2r, 4v, 164rv.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
